Abstract: A two-day search reveals a New Yorker’s relationship with his city, and proves it’s a city that doesn’t keep all of its secrets.
Snippet: A two-day search reveals a New Yorker’s relationship with his city, and proves it’s a city that doesn’t keep all of its secrets.
LeadParagraph: Those who have misplaced personal belongings on the streets of New York know this: The city does not care if you need your keys or wallet back.

Headline.Main: A Lost Bag and a Lost Night, but Not a Lost Cause
